# CARL Agents Domain
# ===================
# Multi-agent specialization architecture. Defines agent boundaries,
# handoff protocols, and orchestration rules.
# Loaded on-demand when parallel work or specialized tasks are needed.
# Compacted 2026-03-19: 18 → 9 rules. Agent types merged into one,
# contracts merged, pipelines merged, cost rules merged.

# ============================================================================
# AGENT TYPES & CONTRACTS
# ============================================================================

# NotebookLM tier system: .claude/skills/notebooklm/SKILL.md
AGENTS_RULE_0=AGENT TYPES & SCOPE: Five agent types with defined boundaries: (1) RESEARCH AGENT — Apollo, LinkedIn, websites, NotebookLM, Fireflies, web search. Input: prospect+company. Output: structured research note. Cannot: draft, update CRM, make strategy calls. (2) DRAFT AGENT — emails, scripts, messages, proposals. Input: research note + PATTERNS.md + framework + history. Output: formatted draft. Cannot: research, update CRM, approve own output. (3) CRM AGENT — Pipedrive reads/writes, deal stages, activities, notes, contacts. Input: action+outcome. Output: confirmed CRM state. Uses RUBE_MULTI_EXECUTE for batching. Cannot: draft, research. (4) AUDIT AGENT — quality scoring, gate verification, pattern analysis, health checks. Input: any output. Output: score+gaps+recommendations. Cannot: fix what it finds (separation of concerns). Must be independent — never audits own work. (5) ORCHESTRATOR — main Claude session. Routes inputs, spawns agents, handles Oliver interaction. Never does work a specialized agent should do.

AGENTS_RULE_1=AGENT CONTRACTS: Input — every agent receives a structured brief: task_type, prospect_name+company, file paths to read, specific deliverable expected, quality rubric reference. Subagents also get: note template path, quality rules path, post-validation instructions. Output — every agent returns: deliverable, self_score (per quality-rubrics.md), confidence level, files_modified list, flags (anything unexpected). Orchestrator reviews flags before presenting to Oliver.

AGENTS_RULE_2=AGENT PIPELINES: Research→Draft: research output becomes draft input. Draft MUST NOT re-research — trusts the note. Insufficient research → draft returns "INSUFFICIENT RESEARCH: [what's missing]" to orchestrator for new research spawn. Draft→Audit: audit scores independently. Score < 7 → back to draft with feedback. Max 2 revision cycles — still < 7 after 2 → escalate to Oliver with both draft and audit notes. Batch: 3+ independent tasks → orchestrator spawns parallel agents, collects results, presents summary. CRM agent handles all writes in batch after others complete.

# ============================================================================
# WHEN TO USE & COST
# ============================================================================

AGENTS_RULE_3=Use specialized agents when: (1) task has clear separation of research/draft/CRM/audit, (2) 3+ independent items can parallelize, (3) audit independence matters (wrap-up scoring), (4) CRM batch operations (save Composio credits). Do NOT spawn agents for: single quick lookups, Oliver-directed edits, conversational exchanges, tasks requiring real-time Oliver feedback loops.

AGENTS_RULE_4=AGENT COST CONTROL: Research agents hitting Apollo/Pipedrive must batch queries. CRM agent uses RUBE_MULTI_EXECUTE_TOOL. Never spawn 3 research agents each calling Apollo — spawn 1 that batches all lookups. Maximum 5 subagents per session unless Oliver approves more. Track agents_spawned_this_session. At 5 → warn: "Agent budget reached. Approve more?"

# ============================================================================
# HARD BOUNDARIES (protected — never retire)
# ============================================================================

AGENTS_RULE_5=HARD BOUNDARY: Research Agent prompt MUST NOT include instructions to draft, update CRM, or approve output. If research agent returns a draft → reject and re-spawn. This prevents scope creep.

AGENTS_RULE_6=HARD BOUNDARY: Draft Agent prompt MUST include research output as input. Draft agent MUST NOT have Apollo/Pipedrive/Fireflies tool access. Needs more research → returns "INSUFFICIENT RESEARCH: [what's missing]" for orchestrator to handle.

AGENTS_RULE_7=HARD BOUNDARY: Audit Agent MUST NOT receive draft agent's self-score. Scores independently. 2+ point divergence → flag for Oliver. This prevents self-grading bias from leaking through context.

AGENTS_RULE_8=ENFORCEMENT LOG: Every subagent spawn logged with: agent_type, task_summary, input_contract, output_contract, boundary_violations detected. Log to brain/system-patterns.md Agent Execution Log section.
